<plot>In this Screen Snapshots entry (production number 3857) Edward G. Robinson (not in archive footage) appears as the viewer, with director Ralph Staub, and narrator/guide to the Hollywood of days gone by. Their are brief (archive footage) informal glimpses of such past silent-and-sound movie stars such as Mary Astor, Grace Moore, Al Joslon, Wallace Beery and many others. Most of the archive footage in this one had been used previously in other Screen Snapshots, possibly make it stock-footage archive-footage.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?482150</url></doc>
